  "title": "Spring block inclined plane",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a block on a ramp that is inclined at an angle theta. The block is pushed against a spring to its left, and an outline of the block is shown to the right, toward the top of the ramp. The distance between the block and its outline is labeled D.\" height=\"86\" src=\"/images/e155bb6bb246bac1ca719ea5d8f304db.png\" width=\"280\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></math></span></span> is at rest on a ramp that is inclined at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Î¸</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> with respect to the horizontal. Frictional forces are considered to be nonnegligible. The block is pushed against a spring and then held in place. The spring is compressed a distance of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></math></span></span>, and the spring is not secured to the block. The block is then released from rest, travels up the incline, and comes to rest after traveling a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown above. Which of the following claims correctly describes the energy of the system under consideration from when the block compressed the spring and when the block has traveled a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> along the incline? Select two answers.</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mechanical energy of the system consisting of the spring increases by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\"><math alttext=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msubsup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mechanical energy of the system consisting of the block does not change.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mechanical energy of the system consisting of the block and Earth increases by more than zero but less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\"><math alttext=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msubsup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mechanical energy of the system consisting of the spring, block, and Earth increases by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\"><math alttext=\"one half, k x sub 1 squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msubsup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
